<h2>Renting equipment</h2>
<h3>Locals Surf School</h3>
<p>Text or email them a day in advance, and they'll put a foam board on the side for you. You can pick it up from their tent at Beach 67th. They're usually on the beach by 8AM -- great if you want to ride early.</p>

<h3>Breakwater Surf</h3>
<p>Located off the train at beach 67th, they open at 8AM on the weekends and 9AM during the week. They have various boards: foam boards and hard top boards (from 6' to 9'). On the weekend during the summer, get there before 10:30AM to be able to find a board to rent. They sell out quickly. <a href="http://breakwatersurfcompany.com/" target="_blank">Visit website</a>.</p>

<h3>Boarders Surf Shop</h3>
<p>Boarders has several locations: 92nd Street, 98th Street and 68th Street (pop up on the beach through the end of September). They open at 10AM in all locations and offer a wide range of boards options: foam boards and hard top boards (from 6' to 9'). The pop up shop only has larger boards. <a href="http://www.boarderssurfshop.com/" target="_blank">Visit website</a>.</p>


<h2>Surfboard lockers</h2>
<p>
If you decide to buy your own board, and to store it at Rockaway Beach, you have a few options:
<ul>
  <li><a href="http://www.boarderssurfshop.com/" target="_blank">Boarders Surf Shop</a> at 92nd Street offers 24/7 locker access for $70/month.</li>
  <li><a href="http://breakwatersurfcompany.com/" target="_blank">Breakwater Surf</a> at 67th Street offers locker access during their opening hours for $40/month.</li>
  <li><a href="http://marina59.com/watersports.html" target="_blank">Marina 59</a> offers locker rentals for $75/month.</li>
  <li>Some surfers also share tiny studio or shack rentals to store their boards.</li>
</ul>
</p>
